Subclass to the OldCountryOverviewMap with methods and functionallity to create the map-boundry.

Help method when adding items to this map.

Adds bua and municipal groups to newItem if it is a point of interest item. The groups are copied from the ssi this poi (other item) belongs to in the other map. Note that the group ids will be ids in the otherMap (underview IDs possible to translate to overview IDs).

Parameters:

otherItem The item corresponding to the new item.
otherMap The map where otherItem is located and from which newItem originates.

bool GMSCountryOverviewMap::applyChangesFromOtherMap (  OldGenericMap *  otherMap,
vector< uint32 >  itemsAffectedInOtherMap,
bool &  coMapChanged
) 
 

Method for applying changes to production country overview maps, typically when adding some extra data or changes from WASP to the maps.

The affected items could have been removed from or added to the otherMap, or simply had some attribute updated. These changes are here transferred to the country overview map.

Parameters:
otherMap The map from which to apply changes, typically an underview map.
itemsAffectedInOtherMap OldItem ids of items that have changed in otherMap.
coMapChanged Outparam that tells if this country overview map was affected by applying the changes.
Returns:
True.

bool GMSCountryOverviewMap::copyCoPolFilteringFromMap (  GMSCountryOverviewMap *  otherMap,
const char *  breakPointsFileName
) 
 

Update the country polygon of this co map, by copying the copying the country polygon from another co map.

This is used to re-use country polygon filtering from old co maps to new map generation. Will use break points in the break points file to write the countryBorders.txt, the text file that holds filtered country polygon parts. Will set the mapGfxDataIsFiltered flag true in this co map.

Parameters:
otherMap The co map that has the gfx data we want to apply to this cop map.
breakPointsFileName The file containing country polygon break points. NULL if no such file exists.

uint32 GMSCountryOverviewMap::createBorderItems (  const char *  breakPointsFileName  ) 
 

Create border items.

Divides the map gfx data (country polygon) into border parts using info in the country border break points file. The border parts that exist in the borderItems.txt file are used for creating border items in this map. The country polygon must be filtered in coordinate levels first!

Parameters:
breakPointsFileName File with country border break points.
Returns:
Number of border items that were created and added to this co map.

GfxDataFull* GMSCountryOverviewMap::createNewGfxData (  OldItem *  origItem,
uint32  maxDist = MAX_UINT32,
vector< uint16 > *  skippedPolygons = NULL
)  [private]
 

Creates a NEW GfxData based on the GfxData of the specified item.

The polygons are filtered according to maxDist, and only polygons that should be included in the OldCountryOverviewMap are added (OldStreetItems may have polygons with too low roadclass; these will not be added, however if it's optional to have those polygon indices added to an output vector).

Parameters:
origItem The item who's GfxData should be used when creating the new GfxData.
maxDist The maxDist parameter, used when filtering polygons. If maxDist is set to MAX_UINT32, then no filtering is performed.
skippedPolygons Optional parameter. Output parameter. Vector that will be filled with the indices of the polygons that are not included in the returned GfxData..
Returns:
A new GfxData. Note that the caller of this method must handle the destruction of this GfxData.

uint32 GMSCountryOverviewMap::getOverviewIDFast (  uint32  origMapID,
uint32  origItemID
)  [inline, private]
 

Uses a lookuptable so it's not O(n) anymore.

Get the ID on this overview map when the orignal map- and item-ID are known.

Note that buildIDsByOriginalIDsTable() must be called in order to create the lookuptable. This is automatically done in the internalLoad method.

Parameters:
origMapID The ID of the map where the item is located "for real".
origItemID The ID of the item on the map where it is located "for real".
Returns:
The ID of the item in this map.

void GMSCountryOverviewMap::makeUniqueNames (  ItemTypes::itemType  itemType,
ItemTypes::pointOfInterest_t  poiType = ItemTypes::nbr_pointOfInterest,
OldItem *  checkItem = NULL
) 
 

Loop through all items of a certain type (for instance bua) and make sure that there are unique names for all of them.

Different items with the same official name will get a new, unique name consisting of the old name + the name of the municipal it is located in.

Generally bua:s and citycentre poi:s should have unique names.

Parameters:
itemType The item type that should have unique names.
poiType In case itemType is pointOfInterestType then specify which kind of poi-type it is.
checkItem If provided the method checks if this item (typically a city centre poi added to production maps) needs to be assigned a new unique name. If so, it does.

bool GMSCountryOverviewMap::mergeStreetSegments (   )

Street segments will be merged between intersections of other streetsegments. The resulting street segments are then filtered.

void GMSCountryOverviewMap::updateAttributes (  OldItem *  overviewItem,
OldItem *  otherItem,
OldGenericMap *  otherMap
)  [private]
 

Update the attribute values of an overviewItem to the values of another item.

Typically used when applying changes to country overview production maps from underview maps. This method updates attributes that requires lookup of true ids in overview/underview, e.g. groups (from underview to overview group id). It also updates names and gfxData.

Parameters:
overviewItem The overviewItem to update attributes for.
otherItem The item from which to get attribute values.
otherMap The map where otherItem is located.

void GMSCountryOverviewMap::updateGroupIDs (  OldItem *  item  )  [private]
 

Help method when updating group ids for all items in the map.

Update groups for one item so they refer to item ids in this map istead of item ids in the original maps. If one group does not exist in this map it is removed from the item.

Parameters:
item The item for which group ids should be updated.

void GMSCountryOverviewMap::updateUniqueNames (  OldItem *  checkItem  )  [private]
 

Check if a new item (typically added when applying changes to production maps) needs to have a unique name.

If so, a unique name is added to the item and any items that had the same (official) name. Group ids for these item(s) must be correct before calling this method.

Parameters:
checkItem The item which (perhaps) should be given a unique name.
